headlines.description: — The Chicago Bears weren’t too concerned about appearances. All that mattered was that they came out on top.
headlines.shortLinkText: Foreman runs for TD, Bears beat Panthers 16-13 to boost their shot at the top pick in the draft

events.name: Indianapolis Colts at New England Patriots

headlines.description: — Jonathan Taylor ran for a first-quarter touchdown and Mac Jones threw a crucial interception in the fourth quarter and the Indianapolis Colts held on for a 10-6 win over New England Patriots in Germany on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jonathan Taylor runs for early TD and Colts hold off Patriots 10-6 in Germany

headlines.description: — C.J. Stroud keeps showing he is the most exciting rookie quarterback in the NFL since ... well, since Joe Burrow.
headlines.shortLinkText: C.J. Stroud leads another game-winning drive, Texans edge Bengals 30-27 on last-second field goal

events.name: New Orleans Saints at Minnesota Vikings

headlines.description: — This latest stop in Minnesota on Joshua Dobbs' seven-year, seven-team NFL journey has become his most eventful experience in less than two weeks.
headlines.shortLinkText: Vikings top Saints 27-19 for 5th straight win on Dobbs' dazzling half, Winston's late INTs

events.name: Green Bay Packers at Pittsburgh Steelers

headlines.description: — Najee Harris stopped paying attention to the circumstances long ago. Maybe because they almost never change for the Pittsburgh Steelers.
headlines.shortLinkText: Running backs shine early, defense shines late as Steelers slip past Green Bay with 23-19 victory

events.name: Tennessee Titans at Tampa Bay Buccaneers

headlines.description: — Mike Evans sat on the bench, staring at his hands in disbelief.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mayfield throws for 278 yards, 2 TDs to help Buccaneers stop 4-game skid with 20-6 win over Titans

headlines.description: — The San Francisco 49ers are Super Bowl contenders once again.
headlines.shortLinkText: 49ers dominate Jaguars 34-3 to end a 3-game skid and look like Super Bowl contenders again

headlines.description: — The Cleveland Browns have received a lot of ridicule for the massive contract they gave Deshaun Watson last year.
headlines.shortLinkText: Watson rallies Browns from 14 down in 4th to 33-31 win over Ravens, tightening AFC North

headlines.description: — Kyler Murray and his surgically repaired right knee were in trouble for a brief moment on the final drive of the fourth quarter.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kyler Murray leads game-winning drive in return from ACL injury as Cardinals beat Falcons 25-23

events.name: Detroit Lions at Los Angeles Chargers

headlines.description: — Dan Campbell wanted to make sure his team had the ball until the last second, even if it meant passing up a chance to take the lead.
headlines.shortLinkText: Goff, Lions outlast Herbert, Chargers 41-38 on Patterson's last-second field goal

events.name: New York Giants at Dallas Cowboys

headlines.description: — Dak Prescott was told his Dallas Cowboys had just beaten the New York Giants by 72 points combined in the two meetings of the NFC East rivals this season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Prescott accounts for 5 TDs, Cowboys rout Giants again 49-17 for 12th straight home win

headlines.description: — Given the opportunity for some more heroics in the closing minutes of the fourth quarter, Geno Smith was nearly flawless.
headlines.shortLinkText: Geno Smith's big throws and Jason Myers' walk-off field goal lift Seahawks past Commanders 29-26

events.name: New York Jets at Las Vegas Raiders

headlines.description: — On a night when Josh Jacobs finally ended his 100-yard dry spell, he couldn't quite forget the fumble that gave the New York Jets life late in the game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jacobs rushes for 116 yards as Raiders improve to 2-0 under Pierce, beat Jets 16-12

headlines.description: — Broncos kicker Wil Lutz made good on his do-over field-goal attempt, much like Denver has done in rebounding from one of its most embarrassing defeats in franchise history.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lutz is good on second chance with 36-yard field goal in Broncos' 24-22 win over Bills
